frameDefinitions: An Experiencer can be described as having an emotion as induced by a Stimulus.
A Payer gives up (or potentially gives up) the use of an Asset (generally money) in order to achieve an Intended_event.
One Part of a larger Whole has been mentioned, is inferrable, or is available in the discourse setting and the previously unmentioned part, the Rest, is now mentioned.
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
These are words relating to emptying containers and clearing areas of some substance or items.
A Person is in a state of prosperity and/or renown after some period of development or hardship in an Endeavor.
frameExamples: The children <t>enjoyed</t> noise games and sing-songs.
It 'll <t>cost</t> Sandra's parents fifty grand a year for her to attend that school.
The lenses , like the <t><fex name='Rest'>rest</fex></t> of the exoskeleton, are made of calcite.
The players <t>emptied</t> the bucket over his head.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is the person or sentient entity that experiences or feels the emotions.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the person, event, or state of affairs that evokes the emotional response in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Experiencer</fen> has an emotion as caused by the <fen>Stimulus</fen>.
The role <fen>Goods</fen> is the item(s) whose price is being assessed.  <fen>Goods</fen> is usually an External Argument:
The person whose <fen>Asset</fen> is given up in order to achieve an <fen>Intended_event</fen>.  This role is often expressed as INI.
The price of or payment made for the Goods.
The event that the <fen>Payer</fen> brings about by deploying the <fen>Asset</fen>.
The time when a transaction takes place.
A <fen>Part</fen> of a larger <fen>Whole</fen> that has been mentioned in prior discourse or is available in the discourse setting.
The previously unmentioned part of the <fen>Whole</fen>.
The larger entitiy or group that is fully made up of the <fen>Part</fen> and the <fen>Rest</fen>.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the entity that does the emptying.
The <fen>Theme</fen>, when overtly expressed, invariably occurs in a PP Complement headed by 'of'.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the region or container which is emptied of something.  In this frame, the <fen>Source</fen> occurs as an NP Object.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient force which instigates the emptying.
The time at which the emptying takes place.
The location where the emptying takes place.
A sentient being or group of beings that is prosperous or well known after being involved in some <fen>Endeavor</fen>.
An event that the <fen>Person</fen> is involved in which leads to their state of prosperity or renown.
The time when the <fen>Entity</fen> is determined to be successful.
listRoleExamples: A holiday in Europe is very expensive <fex>for me</fex>.
No, they've got a special on; it's really cheap there <fex>on Tuesdays</fex>
the GP had stipulated counselling as a complement <fex>to medication</fex>
You should try to persuade the <fex>rest</fex> of the family to do so whatever their personal opinions
The Beaujolais Nouveau is dazzling <fex>in freshness</fex>.
<fex>A basic washing</fex> can degrease your workclothes.
The prisoners were deloused <fex>in June and August</fex>.
<fex>He</fex> became a success at the age of 25.
Looking back, I had a very successful <fex>career</fex>.
After 20 years of hard work, he finally made it as an artist <fex>in '84</fex>.
